es and historical events. Concentrating on the work of nonphilosophical authors such as the historian Thucydides and the tragedian Euripides, the author presents a portrait of a restless and spirited age engaged in an adventure of reason.Originally published in 1975.The Princeton Legacy Library uses the latest print-on-demand technology to again make available previously out-of-print books from the distinguished backlist of Princeton University Press. These editions preserve the original texts of these important books while presenting them in durable paperback and hardcover editions. The goal of the Princeton Legacy Library is to vastly increase access to the rich scholarly heritage found in the thousands of books published by Princeton University Press since its founding in 1905.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aPhilosophy, Ancient. 0aReason. 0aSophists (Greek philosophy). 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Legacy Lib. eBook Package 1931-1979z978311042684708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Legacy Lib. eBook Package Philosophyz978311041356408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140087120940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400871209423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400871209.jpg  a978-3-11-041356-4  Princeton Legacy Lib. eBook Package Philosophy  a978-3-11-042684-7  Princeton Legacy Lib. eBook Package 1931-1979c1931d1979  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSH